<section class={styles["intro-content"]}>
  <p class={styles.lede}>
    Software engineer, seven-plus years in. I work on
    <strong>distributed systems</strong> &mdash; the unglamorous middle
    where queues, caches, and consensus quietly decide whether a
    product feels reliable or doesn&apos;t.
  </p>

  <p>
    Most of my day is spent on the same handful of problems: keeping
    state correct across services, designing APIs that age well, and
    making failure modes obvious before they reach a user. I care
    about the boring parts &mdash; observability, idempotency, the
    second-order effects of a retry &mdash; because that&apos;s usually
    where the bugs live.
  </p>

  <p class={styles.verbs}>
    <span>I build it,</span>
    <span>I ship it,</span>
    <span>I write about what broke.</span>
  </p>

  <p class={styles.cta}>
